<h1 class="bac"><%=program.Item("title")%></h1>

<div class="expand">
<h2 class="bac"><img class="popen" src="../images/clear.gif">Summary:</h2>
<div>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Location: London</li>
	<li>9-week, desk specific programme from June - August</li>
	<li>On track for a minimum of a 2:1 degree classification (or equivalent). Mathematics, Engineering, Physics or Economics background advantageous.</li>
	<li>Treasury - Funding (money market trading  &amp; Analyst roles)</li>
	<li>Treasury - Liquidity Risk Management (Analyst and reporting roles)</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

<div class="expanded">
<h2 class="bac"><img class="pclose" src="../images/clear.gif">Our Business:</h2>
<div>
<p class="bac">Within Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America Merrill Lynch, International Corporate Treasury is a central function whose activities have enterprise-wide impact. The goal of International Corporate Treasury is to optimise shareholder value by providing world-class management of capital, liquidity, interest rate and operational risk. It is also responsible for creating a state of the art framework for managing the tradeoffs between risk and return, and for training and exporting enterprise leaders.</p>
<p class="bac">A career in Treasury allows you to be forward thinking and instrumental to our future strategy. Your day will be varied and challenging, and will allow you to extend your skills in various disciplines, adding value to your role.</p>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<h2 class="bac"><img class="popen" src="../images/clear.gif">Overview:</h2>
<div>
<p class="bac nobr">The summer programme is a precursor to the full-time programme. As a Summer Analyst, you&#39;ll work for nine weeks in roles that mirror the positions of full-time analysts. These could include the following:</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Partnering with the International Treasury Traders who operate within the short-term money markets in order to execute the daily funding strategy and to optimise the management of the bank&#39;s balance sheet</li>
	<li>Support the liquidity risk management team in meeting regulatory requirements at the heart of the response to the global financial crisis</li>
	<li>Analysing data and output from the bank&#39;s Asset/Liability Models to project the core earnings stream (net interest income) of the corporation and evaluating sensitivities to those earnings</li>
	<li>Supporting the capital and liquidity analysis, execution, and maintenance of new structured finance transactions</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<h2 class="bac"><img class="popen" src="../images/clear.gif">Training:</h2>
<div>
<p class="bac nobr">The programme is designed to help you decide whether our offer matches your aspirations and includes:</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>One week induction and training programme with classroom instruction</li>
	<li>A buddy and mentoring programme</li>
	<li>Summer Senior Speaker Series, featuring global  &amp; divisional presentations by top executives</li>
	<li>Opportunities to interact with senior bankers and network with peers</li>
	<li>Constructive feedback sessions through performance evaluations</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<h2 class="bac"><img class="popen" src="../images/clear.gif">Qualifications:</h2>
<div>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>On track for a minimum of a 2:1 degree classification (or equivalent). Mathematics, Engineering, Physics or Economics background advantageous</li>
	<li>Impressive academic qualifications, and consistently strong performance in A-levels and university will need to be combined with drive, innovation and an understanding of global financial markets, products and tools</li>
	<li>An appetite for risk taking and/or risk management also essential</li>
	<li>An ability to work in a fast paced environment whilst multi tasking  &amp; interacting with a wide variety of people. Strong quantitative and analytical skills, ideally supported by a good understanding of statistics, will be important</li>
	<li>You should also have teamwork and problem-solving skills, a willingness to accept responsibility, ask tough questions, and have a pragmatic approach</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

